%N A396736 Decimal expansion of Sum_{k>=1} (-1)^(k+1)*H(k,2)/k^2, where H(k,2) = A007406(k)/A007407(k) is the k-th generalized harmonic number of order 2.
%C A396736 Let s(p,q) = Sum_{n >= 1} (-1)^(n+1)*H(n,p)/n^q, then s(1,1) = A076788, s(1,2) = A233090, and s(2,2) is this constant.
%D A396736 Ali Shadhar Olaikhan, An Introduction to the Harmonic Series and Logarithmic Integrals, 2021, p. 243, eq. (4.144).
%H A396736 Ali Shadhar Olaikhan, <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/373488370">An Introduction to the Harmonic Series and Logarithmic Integrals</a>, 2nd ed., 2023, section 4.3.8, p. 310, eq. (4.87).
%H A396736 Cornel Ioan Vălean, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-030-02462-8">(Almost) Impossible Integrals, Sums, and Series</a>, Springer International Publishing, 2019, section 4.51, p. 310, eq. (4.86), section 5.51, p. 326, section 6.51, pp. 498-502.
%H A396736 <a href="/index/Ha#harmonic">Index entries for sequences related to harmonic numbers</a>.
%F A396736 Equals log(2)^4/6 - log(2)^2*zeta(2) + 7*log(2)*zeta(3)/2 - 51*zeta(4)/16 + 4*Li_4(1/2).
